author: Tan JR
text:
Extremely Disappointing Experience - Constant Delays & No Communication

I strongly advise against signing up for a membership with AF Aljundied 119. I signed up based on the promise that the gym would open in February 2025, with the latest opening date being the end of March 2025.

It is now late April 2025, and the gym is still not open. What's worse is the complete lack of proactive communication from their side. Throughout this period, there have been absolutely no updates unless I reached out to them directly.

When I inquired about the delays, I was met with a series of excuses ranging from contractor issues to safety check delays, none of which came with a concrete, reliable new opening date. Now, they vaguely suggest a "late April" opening, but given the track record, I have very little confidence in this.

Their suggested "solution" of using sister gyms is impractical and inconvenient, requiring members to book appointments just to get a workout in ‚Äì shifting the burden entirely onto the customer. They have shown zero accountability for the significant delays and the inconvenience caused to members who signed up in good faith based on their initial promises.

Despite failing to open on time and leaving existing members hanging, they are still actively advertising and signing up new people. This lack of transparency and disregard for customers who have already paid is unacceptable.

Save yourself the frustration and uncertainty. Look for other established gyms or new openings that value clear communication and actually deliver on their timelines. This has been a thoroughly disappointing experience, and I regret signing up.

author: A
text:
Signed up in January when I saw the gym offering a pre-sale discount. The staff said the tentative opening date would be 18 Feb. Now it's end April and the gym is still not ready.

The management then decided to give access to only 4 gyms (which are all very far from where I live) during STAFFED HOURS. Why can't they just give us the keyfob that we have paid for? It already doesn't make sense that we have to pay for an access card on top of the membership fee when it is literally just an app to enter the gym.

Many other members also asked about the opening date and the gym's response was a mere copy paste talking about the safety issues, with no confirmed date. We can't even get a refund!

I would strongly advise against signing up at this gym. Save your money and sign at another outlet.

I have to approach them to ask, all I heard were excuses about ‚Äúsafety issues‚Äù or ‚Äúcontractors.‚Äù I understand delays happen, but as the owner or management, that‚Äôs your responsibility, not something paying customers should be made to bear.

I requested to cancel my membership and get a refund due to the lack of service ‚Äî but they refused to return any money. Extremely disappointing.

Would not recommend based on my experience.

author: Felix R
text:
Don‚Äôt waste your money here. This whole experience feels like a complete scam. I signed up back in December when they told me the tentative opening date would be 18 Feb. Since then, it‚Äôs been one delay after another ‚Äî pushed to late Feb/early March, then end March/early April. It‚Äôs now the end of April and there‚Äôs still ZERO updates on when (or if) this place is ever going to open.

Worse, the communication has been absolutely appalling. At first they said it‚Äôs due to delays on the contractor because of CNY. Then, when it‚Äôs past the promised 18 Feb opening date, they suddenly shifted the narrative to ‚Äúsafety issues.‚Äù When I asked via WhatsApp if this was a structural safety issue, they confirmed that it was ‚Äî but refused to provide any further clarification.

What kind of safety issue are we even talking about here? Structural cracks? Load-bearing columns being hacked without a permit? Load bearing walls or structural beams hacked away without permit? These are serious concerns that any customer deserves to be informed about. But instead of transparency, they‚Äôre just dodging questions and hiding behind vague statements.

It‚Äôs honestly infuriating. They had time to update social media daily back in December and January to promote memberships and rake in pre-opening payments ‚Äî but now they can‚Äôt even be bothered to give a simple, honest update about what‚Äôs going on? No proper announcements, no estimated dates, no transparency. Just the same useless copy-pasted replies that say absolutely nothing.

This whole situation is shady and completely unprofessional. At this point, I regret ever signing up. If you haven‚Äôt paid yet ‚Äî don‚Äôt. And if you have, good luck getting any answers.

**update: they changed the opening date to May 2025 but still tbc üíÄüíÄüíÄüíÄ

author: J J
text:
I deeply regret signing up for a membership at Anytime Fitness (AF119) due to their complete lack of transparency and accountability. During registration, I was told the gym would open on 18 February 2025. However, I later learned that the opening was delayed to late February or early March‚Äîa minimum delay of 2-6 weeks. They then claimed the 18 February date provided during registration was always ‚Äútentative‚Äù and never confirmed.

When reviewing the membership agreement to check cancellation policies, I noticed the registration form I signed was missing a start date. When I asked the gym why this was omitted, they shifted the blame onto me for not clarifying the details. It is their responsibility to provide accurate and complete information during sign-up, yet they failed to do so.

What‚Äôs more, they now claim the membership contract wasn‚Äôt issued because the start date wasn‚Äôt confirmed. So, what exactly was the membership agreement I signed? Why weren‚Äôt customers informed that there is both a membership agreement and a separate membership contract? Can anyone verify the existence of this separate contract? Even if that‚Äôs the case, what was the purpose of signing the document if it doesn‚Äôt even count as a proper agreement? Charging customers without a confirmed start date or clear terms is not just misleading - it‚Äôs outright unethical.

When I requested a refund, I repeatedly asked for the full terms and conditions to justify their actions, but they refused. Instead, they blamed renovation delays. This is their business - why should the customer bear the consequences of their delays?

This entire experience may just be about a refund of $183, which I now realize I will likely never get back from a business with such unethical practices. However, I am sharing this because it is unacceptable for customers to be misled and blamed for the company‚Äôs lack of transparency and accountability. I want to warn others from being duped into this same situation.

If you‚Äôre considering joining this gym, proceed with extreme caution. Ensure every single detail is clarified in writing because transparency clearly isn‚Äôt a priority for them.
